#pythontip by @PyPrinciples:

You can use | and & for set union and intersection. 

>>> {1, 2} & {2, 3}
{2}
>>> {1, 2} | {2, 3}
{1, 2, 3}

Add elements of one dictionary to another with the update() method:

>>> d1 = {'a' : 1, "b" : 2}
>>> d2 = {'c' : 2, "d" : 42, "a" : 3}
>>> d1.update(d2)
>>> d1
{'a': 3, 'b': 2, 'c': 2, 'd': 42}

